Working with annotations
========================

Add annotations to mark any component with user-specific information for future use.

Annotations do not impact formatting in any way.

Creating annotations
--------------------

Create annotations like this:

<abjad>
annotation = marktools.Annotation('annotated information')
</abjad>

<abjad>
annotation
print repr(annotation) <hide
</abjad>

Attaching annotations to a component
------------------------------------

Attach annotations to a component by calling the annotation on the component:

<abjad>
note = Note("c'4")
</abjad>

<abjad>
annotation(note)
</abjad>

<abjad>
annotation
print repr(annotation) <hide
</abjad>

Creating annotations and attaching them to components in one step
-----------------------------------------------------------------

You can combine the two steps above like this:

<abjad>
another_annotation = marktools.Annotation('special information about note')(note)
</abjad>

<abjad>
another_annotation
print another_annotation <hide
</abjad>

